This paper deals with the problem of finding control policies for partially observable Markov decision processes, which is a fundamental problem in artificial intelligence and machine learning. Therefore, cs.AI is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the computational complexity of finding optimal policies, which suggests that it may belong to cs.LG (machine learning) and cs.DS (data structures and algorithms). Additionally, the paper deals with control policies in the context of systems and control theory, which suggests that it may belong to cs.SY (systems and control) and cs.MA (multi-agent systems).
